Let's check the roundtrips:

\[\mathsf{fore}\ f\ (\mathsf{back}\ f\ k)\ a\ a'\]
\[ =  \{\mpair{\elax f} {\mathsf{back}\ f\ k}\ \mpair{\elax a}{a'}\} \]
\[ =  \{(\lambda \bar a . \mpair{(\elax f)\ \bar a}{k\ (\ilax \bar a)\ \{\bar a\}})\ \mpair{\elax a}{a'}\} \]
\[ =  \{ \mpair{(\elax f)\ \bar a}{k\ (\ilax (\mpair{\elax a}{a'}))\ \{\mpair{\elax a}{a'}\}}\} \]
\[ =_\eta  \{ \mpair{(\elax f)\ \bar a}{k\ (\ilax (\mpair{\elax a}{a'}))\ a'}\} \]
\[ =_\eta  k\ (\ilax (\mpair{\elax a}{a'}))\ a' \]
\[ =_h  k\ (\ilax (\elax a))\ a' \]
\[ =  k\ a\ a' \]

\[\mathsf{back}\ f\ (\lambda a \ a'. \mathsf{fore}\ f\ f'\ a\ a')\]
\[=  \{ \lambda \bar a . \mpair{(\elax f)\ \bar a}{(\lambda a \ a'. \mathsf{fore}\ f\ f'\ a\ a')\ (\ilax \bar a)\ \{\bar a\}}\} \]
\[=  \{ \lambda \bar a . \mpair{(\elax f)\ \bar a}{ \mathsf{fore}\ f\ f'\ (\ilax \bar a)\ \{\bar a\} }\} \]
\[=  \{ \lambda \bar a . \mpair{(\elax f)\ \bar a}{ \{\mpair{\elax f} {f'}\ \mpair{\elax (\ilax \bar a)}{\{\bar a\}}\} }\} \]
\[=_\beta  \{ \lambda \bar a . \mpair{(\elax f)\ \bar a}{ \{\mpair{\elax f} {f'}\ \bar a\} }\} \]
\[=_\beta  \{ \lambda \bar a . \mpair{\elax f} {f'}\ \bar a\} \]
\[=_\eta  \{  \mpair{\elax f} {f'}\} \]
\[=_\eta   {f'} \]
